  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Thoughts of Home on the Ninth Day
  author: Seol Son
  language: eng
  text: |-
    On the ninth day, homesickness stirs—
    I remember last year's dwelling.
    We moved to the eastern fields by the bridge,
    where blue mountains frame the door like autumn's tapestry,
    and purple chrysanthemums grow in rows,
    wrapped in the smoke of evening.

    Blessed with books and verse for refined pursuits,
    yet untouched by the dust of carriages and horses.
    Now on the western wind's ancient shore,
    I drift in my small boat along the Biryeong road—
    my heart heavy with longing.
  footnotes:
    - The ninth day of the ninth lunar month was traditionally celebrated in East Asia as a festival of gathering and reflection
    - Biryeong (毗陵) refers to a region in what is now Jiangsu Province, associated with water routes and travel
